HEADWORD: Clematis
<hw>Clem"a*tis</hw> <pr>(kl⟦ecr⟧m"⟦adot⟧*t⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>klhmati`s</grk> brushwood, also (from its long,
lithe branches) clematis. fr. <grk>klh^ma</grk> twig, shoot, fr.
<grk>kla^n</grk> to break off.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
flowering plants, of many species, mostly climbers, having feathery
styles, which greatly enlarge in the fruit; -- called also
<altname>virgin's bower</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clemence</ent>⟦br⟧
